==English==
===Etymology===
From {{L.}} [[#Latin|tectum]] "roof", from [[tego]] "to cover", from [[Ancient Greek]] '''[[τέγος]]''' (''tegos'') "roof", or "any covered room of a house".

===Pronunciation===
*{{IPA|/ˈtɛk.təm/}}

===Noun===
'''tectum'''

# The dorsal portion of the [[midbrain]], containing the [[superior colliculus]] and [[inferior colliculus]]
# The interconnected outer surface of a [[spore]].

===Derived terms===
*[[infratectum]]

===See also===
*[[tegmentum]]
*[[periaqueductal grey]]

===References===
Bear et al. Neuroscience, Exploring the Brain Co. 2001, Lippincot Williams and Wilkins

